rComments: This is the worst professor I had so far. He does not give a single lecture, he just asks to watch videos from his previous lectures from years ago, it seems like he could not be bothered to teach that again. His classes are just him solving questions, and a quiz that happens every week (accounts for 50% of your grade). Don't take this professor!!!
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Graded by few things', 'Tough grader']

rComments: You'll get a quiz for each chapter.

Prof Shiell seems like a very nice guy. His classes aren't super interesting, but it could be cause I don't care about economics. He tends to ramble about things and the notes can sometimes be disorganized. Besides that, he's always willing to answer questions and if you pay attention and study, you can get a good grade!

Lectures are entertaining/funny and actually useful. Emphasizes actually understanding the material and critically analyzing it, rather than memorization, which I find tends to lack in other econ courses. Also a very reasonable grader. Easily my favourite econ prof through my 4 years and a must-take if you're interested in enviromental econ.
Would not take class again. Very hard grader...
His lectures are very long and boring. I honestly feel like I didn't learn anything in this class. I don't recommend this class unless it's a program requirement.
Stay on top of your work and you should be fine. The final can be challenging but passable. Caring as other comments have suggested.
Great prof, really cares about students' success. I love him, one of my favorite profs

He is the most amazing teacher. The class is easy if you really like Math. Attendance is not mandatory but I would suggest you come to class. NO midterms for this class. Just quizzes and final. Beware of the final very very hard even when you study well. The final marks are not allocated equally (so a question can be 18 marks).

Un très bon choix comme prof. Sa première langue est l'anglais mais il fait un réel effort pour ses étudiants francophones. J'ai beaucoup apprécié le format du cours de ECO2518 (4 dissertations, toutes à la maison) au lieu d'exams. Cela rend le cours plus facile à planifier pour les étudiants.

He uses a format where you watch recorded lectures at home, and then do practice problems in class with the prof. We also do a quiz every week instead of one big midterm. I like it better this way, but you really have to stay on top of your work. He's funny and tells cute Dad-jokes, and he really knows his stuff. Overall great prof.

One of the better profs I've had. He is obviously well prepared and knows the material thoroughly. The only bad thing I can say about his course is the new format he tried this year (video lectures that you watch on your own time and then discuss the content in class). It is a lot of work but if you keep on top of things, you'll be fine.
Attend class, take notes on the lecture videos, you'll get a good mark. Very helpful professor if you go to his office hours, he teaches you to learn for yourself. Highly recommended.

Excellent prof! Great sense of humour, keeps his students engaged, and makes the material bearable. The material is challenging, but is essential if students want to continue in advanced micro and macroeconomics. Attend class, listen to  the podcasts, and do the homework, and you can easily do well in his class. His marking schemes are very fair.
Prof. Shiell is very kind and knowledgeable.

Very unusual person. His class humour is mild but he uses the same humor outside classroom which is impossible to talk to him. You can never have a serious conversation with him as he's weird at one-on-one. Class 3145 take it and all his exams are from his assigned assignments.
He is a good and engaging professor. The course itself is very though and the concepts are hard to understand but he does a good job in explaining them as well as he can.
Very good professor, makes material engaging. Allows for a lot of flexibility and autonomy. Great 4th year optional course.
awesome prof
Very nice person. He is ready to help you almost whenever you want. His teaching is interesting too. I like his class and this Prof.
BAD

He's a good teacher. Nice and Helpful. I like his lecture though. You won't feel too boring of learning math with him. He's trying to make math interesting. And he's easygoing with students. I like him. Don't miss his class. He maybe one of the best prof in department of economics.

Mathematical economics was great, I liked his class. Micro3, well nobody understands it well enough, including all the profs that teach it, including myself (I got a really good grade). Shiell is availabe nearly all times for students, he tries his best to help them, unlike some professors (who just suck, I can do sooooo much better).
Tough course

The best ever professor considering helpfulness. You could find him in his office 24/7 and most of the time he was able to help you even when busy with other matters. He really did wanted us to succeed.
You thought the math was tough? You boyz are in for a treat, wait till you do micro3.  LOL

Funny prof & super nice. The course material for math econ is super tough. I found he didn't make things any simplier. I usually didn't understand his explanations. But he's always willing to help at his office hours. He is very friendly and helpful.
